<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="alongside-prep">alongside <strong><em>prep</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əˌlɒŋ'saɪd/    美 /əˌlɔːŋ'saɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>在…旁边；沿着…的边；与…并排：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Children’s prices are shown alongside adult prices.
儿童票价写在成人票价的旁边。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The drivers behind me got impatient, with some speeding up alongside me. 
我后面的司机不耐烦了，有的竟加速与我并排行驶。</p><footer>2011 广东改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>与…一起；与…同时：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The robot is not intended to replace workers, but to work alongside other employees.
这个机器人不是为了替代工人，而是和其他员工一起工作。</p><footer>2015 天津改</footer></div></div>